<p>I built a web service in apache camel running as a bundle on karaf which takes the requests and saves the information in a database.</p>  <p>After this another bundle takes this inserted record, modifies the data and saves it back to the db.</p>  <p>Now I need the response of the original request to contain the modified data so besides the route for the web service that looks like this</p>  <pre><code>&lt;route id="cxf"&gt;     &lt;from uri="cxf:bean:getHopEndpoint" /&gt;     &lt;recipientList&gt;         &lt;simple&gt;direct:${header.operationName}&lt;/simple&gt;     &lt;/recipientList&gt; &lt;/route&gt; &lt;route id="getHop"&gt;     &lt;from uri="direct:getHop" /&gt;     &lt;process ref="getHopToDbProcessor" /&gt;     &lt;to         uri="sql:INSERT INTO myTable (field1, field2) VALUES (:#field1, :#field2)"/&gt; &lt;/route&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I would need another one like this</p>  <pre><code>&lt;route id="cxfResponse"&gt;     &lt;from uri="sql:SELECT * FROM myTable"/&gt;     &lt;!-- to web service response in any way --&gt; &lt;/route&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there any way to do this?</p>